      "description": "Available is a 2002 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Titanium Silver. This example is powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing, producing a sharp 333 hp. The power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a variable M Differential Lock. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive VANOS top-end refresh and a reinforced rear subframe to ensure chassis longevity. The suspension geometry is maintained with upgraded polyurethane bushings and KONI adjustable dampers for improved turn-in response. While the body exhibits minor road wear consistent with its well-maintained 'good' condition, the drivetrain remains exceptionally tight and responsive. This is a driver-focused machine with excellent mechanical provenance.",
